The Chronicle Michael Magoronga, Midlands Correspondent NINE families including doctors, physiotherapist, nurses and an administrator lost property worth thousands of dollars after a fire destroyed staff quarters at Kwekwe General Hospital this morning. <img class="alignnone wp-image-550855 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Kwekwe General Hospital Medical Superintendent, Dr Patricia Mapanda confirmed the incident. <img class="alignnone wp-image-550858 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “I can confirm that a fire broke out, razed one of the staff residences and destroyed property. The staff members including doctors lost almost everything as they did not get time to remove their property,” said Dr Mapanda. <img class="alignnone wp-image-550857 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Kwekwe-hosp-fire-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> She said no one was injured in the inferno.